  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And when she finished, she just folded her their hands and the needles, and she expired.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "It was-- was-- [INAUDIBLE] was passing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "The business that my grandfather was in, you know, also ceased to exist.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And because of the very, very difficult times that prevailed in those days, my father started seeking employment and went out to the town of Bielsko which was about 60 miles, 96 kilometers, from Krakow.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "It was a town close to the Czech and German border.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "It was long before the [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "Silesia. ?] And found employment in a large butcher shop there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "After a few months, he brought my mother and myself to the city of Bielsko, and we found an apartment in an adjacent small town suburb which was called Biala.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "It was in a different-- it was the district of Krakow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "I enrolled in a Jewish day school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "And I spent the following four years in the school, the fourth, fifth, sixth, and seventh grade.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "The school only had seven grades.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "And after a short amount of time, my father enrolled me in a [NON-ENGLISH] because he felt that the Jewish education at that particular school was not-- you know, would not complete my Jewish, you know, knowledge.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 90,
      "text": "But because of the fact that I knew less than other boys of my age, I was put in the class of boys about two years younger than I was, and I just didn't feel comfortable.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 91,
      "text": "And I started skipping class.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after a certain amount of time, my father went to pay the tuition, and the rabbi told him, why are you paying?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Your son is not attending.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So my father was perplexed because he used to see me leave home in the afternoon, supposedly going to the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
